I have set SourceTree to launch Beyond Compare 4 as my external merge tool.  This worked fine.

One time, I had a few files that needed conflicts resolving so I ticked the checkbox in the corner of the dialog that pops up before launching the external merge tool.  I can't recall exactly what the text was on the checkbox, but it sounded like I was temporarily stopping the dialog appearing.  Unfortunately, what has happened is that it has permanently switched off launching my external merge tool.  Instead, when I get a file with conflicts, the file immediately is listed in both the *Staged* and *Unstaged* panes and the file contains the standard Git text-based markers for conflicts (shown below).

In desperation, I tried a complete reinstall to turn back on the launching of my external merge tool but even this has not worked.  I am guessing that SourceTree has saved settings somewhere (which it must have done because all my remote accounts were already populated after the reinstall).

I'd like to know how I can fix this.  And my suggested improvement is to get rid of the dialog that launches before an external merge tool is launched and certainly re-word the checkbox to make it plain that you are about to *permanently* turn off the external merge.

 

Kind wishes ~ Patrick
